title: WI State Road Championship --  Spring Prairie Road
Nature Valley Bike Fest Gran Fondo
John Hatherly Mid Century Ride - Waupaca
description:
John Hatherly is an avid cyclist an recently turned 50.  As a surprise for his 50th, his wife honored him with a bike ride in his honor.  The Hatherly\'s have a home in Waupaca and wanted to share this ride with the community.  Multiple distance rides are available for all to enjoy.  In addition the event will provide scholarships to multiple graduating Waupaca High School seniors.

This event has donated over $40,000 in scholarships in just two years.
course:
There are multiple distances that will all begin and end at Waupaca High School.  Because of the flower-petal design of the course, you can build your own distance based on how you feel that day.  Standard distances include 12, 20, 50, 62, 70 and 100 miles.  The 100 mile course will be two loops of the 50 mile distance.
 
There will be a two rest stop locations.  The first will be at high school.  Riders will pass this rest stop at mile mile 20 and again at mile 50.  In addition, there will be a rest stop at mile 32.  100 mile riders will also see this rest stop at mile 82.

course: Course will be in back of Mitchell Park.
directions: Exit Layton Avenue and turn left immediately to reach rear parking lot.

title: USGP Cyclocross-Planet Bike Cup
description: The 2012 Planet Bike Cup takes place at Angell Park Speedway in Sun Prairie, WI on September 22 and 23, 2012. It kicks off the 2012 Exergy US Gran Prix of Cyclocross p/b Greenware.   The two days of racing features races for Juniors, Masters through the Elite/Professional categories.
course: The course is challenging with terrain for every style of rider.   It features a challenging run-up; technical descent and wide open straights.   When it is muddy it is extremely slick and when dry very very fast.
registration: Online registration open on August 10, 2012 at 9am eastern and closes on September 21st, 2012 at 10pm eastern.   Pre-registration is MANDATORY for all Elite Categories.   On-site registration will be available for all other categories and a $10 per day late fee will be charged.   Registration is available on BikeReg.com.
notes: NO REFUNDS.   Race will be run rain or shine.
directions:
Angell Park Speedway is located at 300 Park Street in Sun Prairie, WI, 53590.  

The course is located 1.1 miles from the host hotel. Head east on Main Street for .8 miles, turn RIGHT onto Market and follow Market to Park Street and the entrance to the venue.

From Madison: 
Take US-151 N/E Washington Ave and Continue to follow US-151 N. Take exit 101 for Main St toward US-151 Bus - Slight right at W Main St. Turn right at Market St and continue on Park St

title: E.T. Twilight Cross
description: Wisconsin\'s First Evening Cyclocross Race-Under the Lights!
course: Rolling course with fast grass, sand and quick hills. Centerpiece being the giant mound that will be traversed multiple ways!
registration:
PreReg available on BikeReg.com.
Registration opens at 2:30pm and closes 20 minutes before each event. Entry fee includes USAC Insurance and WCA surcharge. Riders without a USA Cycling racing license must purchase a \"USAC One Day License\" or an annual USAC license.
notes: Please note schedule of races is different than the rest of the series.
directions: Park is located at Rossmiller Sports Complex -3090 Graydon Ave, East Troy, WI 53120 adjacent to the High School.
